Q2:
If John Snow had collected data only from local hospitals, his dataset would have been incomplete and not fully accurate,
because not all sick people or people who died would have gone to the hospital. This means he would have missed many cases.
One of the most important effects of this is that the connection between the cholera cases and the water pump might not have been as clear. 
He may have only seen that there were many cases in general, but he would not have understood as clearly where the cases were coming from or what source they were connected to.
So in the end, this could have made his conclusions weaker or less accurate.

