Q3:
A modern example of “miasma” today could be the idea that if a worker spends more time in the office, then this means they are more productive. 
This is a common idea, but it is not always true.
Sometimes a person may spend many hours in the office without doing their best work, 
while another person may work from home and finish their tasks in a better and more efficient way.
So if we test this idea carefully with data, we may find that being seen in the office does not always mean higher productivity, 
and that real productivity should be measured by results and quality of work, not only by physical presence.
